google-droid-fonts: google-droid-fonts (font family from Google's Android project)
google-droid-fonts:
google-droid-fonts: The Droid typeface family was designed in the fall of 2006 by
google-droid-fonts: Ascender's Steve Matteson, as a commission from Google to create
google-droid-fonts: a set of system fonts for its Android platform.  The goal was to
google-droid-fonts: provide optimal quality and comfort on a mobile handset when 
google-droid-fonts: rendered in application menus, web browsers and other screen text.
